<br><font size=3><b>36th Rank</b></font></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#353535><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ussymbiant.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ssymbiant</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 98<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/24/01 10:37:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbloodcirclefrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Yin and Yang</span><hr size=1> Soulshiver stared in vain at the plain wooden wall. Summoning every ounce of concentration he tried to re-establish the communication that had just transpired. “Wait,” he said aloud, “My hands were like this.”  He quickly reassumed what he felt was his original position and tried his utmost to center his thoughts on that gloomy forest scene where he had seen Centuri beset by the Dark Host.  His continued efforts to continue the transcontinental communication was in vain, however, as the only thing that was now audible was the painful heartbeats emanating from his own chest.  How he established the communication in the first place was beyond him.  Now of certain things he was sure of: One, that it was truly Centuri, the Feir’Dal enigma that has appeared before him, so real in fact that he was certain that he could smell the smells of the forest that surrounded her and the smells…of Orcs!  Secondly, though he watched from a 3rd person perspective her attacking and easily overtaking the Orcan marauders, he was certain that she was oblivious to the stealthy grace that was unmistakably his brother, coming upon her unprotected, unguarded flank.  Finally, as a miasma of guilt wracked Soulshivers form, he was aware that he was at fault for the suffering that Centuri was undoubtedly to receive, but also that due to his lack of iniative, the entirety of Blood Circle was about to meet its most perilous adventure.  For in one fell blow, his brother, insignificant in so many ways, has for once, found the one weakness that his Elder brother had ever displayed…the love for another.<br>
<br>
Soulshiver hesitated outside the door to the guildhall in the which he had entered so many times in the past.  For the first time, he questioned if he had made the proper choice in including his Brothers and Sisters in a quest that would most certainly lead to suffering and perhaps even their deaths.  But memory strengthened his resolve. He remembered the countless battles he’d undergone with this motley crew and recommitted the memory of why he’d chosen this path of becoming a member of this great guild in the first place.  In his pausing, he could hear the laughter echo merrily from the seams of the Hall as he was certain Dohpaz was drinking the majority of them under the table.  The fact that it was only 10:00 in the morning did not deter him from this train of thought…he knew his Family too well. He stepped to the doorway and pushed the heavy oak door open to hopefully, temporarily arrest the flow of alcohol.  As Soulshiver walked through the entrance, the conversation immediately turned into cheers of welcome as they quickly found a seat for him at the common table.  Itno, more perceptive to Soulshiver’s typically unreadable expressions was instantly aware that his friend was burdened heavily with something and set out at once to lighten his morose brothers mood.  “Soul, ya bag of maggots, why can’t you for once, step in here with a bloody smile!”, Itno said with candor.  To that statement the whole host raised a glass and generally cheered Itno on in his quest.  Soulshiver, at their comic display couldn’t help but smile to the which the crowd cheered on and Dohpaz, thus encouraged, summoned more beer for his thirsty friends.  Seeing that he would quickly lose his friends attention to Dohpaz’s summoning Art, Soulshiver leapt to a tabletop and said, “My friends, I’ve dire news.”  The crowd fell silent as they knew that Soulshiver was about some serious business.  Even Dohpaz and Thorvan fell silent in an awkward embrace that left Dohpaz hanging in a spectacular gnome wedgie.  “Brothers, Sisters, I’ve come upon some dire tidings…one of our own…” Soulshiver hesitated as carefully hidden emotions choked and constricted his throat, “Centuri…has been taken by force by one of my Household Dy’Truin.  This capture of our Sister should have been easily foreseeable.  Yet, as many of you know, I’ve been at odds with myself selfishly seeking answers when they’ve been so readably available to me.  Due to my actions, or lack of them, I’ve enabled, perhaps, our greatest enemy to capture one…loved…by us.”  Zarius, a stern expression on his face, asked, “Soulshiver, what do you know?  What can you tell us?  More importantly what are we going to do?”  At those questions the guildhall erupted into shouts of vengeance, plans for slaughter, and a call for arms.  Soulshiver sighed inwardly as he knew then that his feelings were justified; his Family would stand by him.  Soulshiver loudly cleared his throat, “Circle, though somehow, I’ve allowed this tragedy to happen, I will not allow this effort to bring ruin to our dear friend and to our great Guild.  I know this Enemy.  I know what he wants.  I know how he thinks he will get it…yet, I’ve a surprise for that bucket of puss, the Gods have granted for me as a brother.  A surprise to the like that Norrath has yet to see, Blood Circle united with all strengths common.  I need maps of Neriak and the missing companions of our host, gathered.  Dohpaz, summon something stimulating…its gonna be a long night.”<br>
<br>
The plan was much debated but was finally decided thus:<br>
<br>
The invasion of Neriak would consist of 3 parts.  One a group lead by Kamal, the guilds ugliest and only Troll would with Kkallel, the guilds smelliest and only Ogre would besieges the front gate and the Neriaks Foreign Quarter with spiderlings, skeletons, bears, and any other common creature in Netkolus Forest.  The pandemonium, Kamal assured everyone, would be spectacular, much like his 166th birthday in Feerott where half of the town and most of the swamp had actually burned, despite the downpour of the rain that was present that day.  After creating the mayhem that we hoped they would create, they were to lodge themselves at the bar and get smashing drunk, enough so that they would have the constant eye of every guardsman in a 10 mile radius.  Secondly, a force consisting of Soulshiver, Itno, Gofar, Avaya, Abbyss, and Hinamar would assault the Hall of the Dead visibly in search of Centuri.  This group was founded under much debate, for Soulshiver was certain, that though Fergussen with the help of Anouris and Abbyss tracked Centuri to its depths, would not be there.  In fact, Soulshiver was certain that  she would be far away from its location, and that we would not be unable to locate Centuri’s position at all until the trap set in the Hall of the Dead had been sprung.  The idea, which was to no one’s liking, was that the 6 set off on their suicidal plunge into the Hall of Dead, lasting for as long as they could before Gofar set off an evacuation, leaving Soulshiver behind to whatever devices he could devise.  He assured them that he would be able to feign his death long enough for his brother to arrive.  And thus enters our 3rd group consisting of Thorvan, Masius, Morbidon, Kannushi, Utaldain, and Fergussen.  Soulshiver believed that when the word of the attack came to Tyvlain, he’d set out at once to collect his brother.  He’d readily believe that Blood Circle would leave one of their own behind after the foiled and Centuri-less expedition led to failure.  Better yet, Soulshiver felt that the forces his brother could have collected for this entrapment might be sufficient to have slain any normal group of adventurers.  Fergussen was to track and locate Tyvlain the moment he left his place of hiding, as Soulshiver was once again certain that that was where she would be kept.  The sole goal of the 3rd group was to, under Invisibility, find Centuri, slay her immediate captors, and have Masius gate the entire group to a predetermined location.  The plans were gone over and over again, ‘til every detail had been firmly embedded with every participant.  When the confidence came that they have covered everything, the entire Circle prepared equipment that would be needed for the assault.  After a magical circle of protection had been set on the Hall, the Guild took to their favorite sleeping spots and fell as if dead.  However, though Soulshiver had to took to his bed, at an appointed hour he crept silently back to the common room.  Itno, Anouris, Xairious, Grendul, Blacko, and Utaldain silently awaited him.  “Dark Brothers, thank you for meeting me at this hour.  It is our hour truly, isn’t it?” Soulshiver said with an evil grin.  The gathered assembly smiled and nodded their agreement.  “Anouris, Xairious, Grendul, and Blacko- you are group four. When my brother comes to gloat over my corpse, it will not take him long to realize my ruse.  He will undoubtedly take me to my ancestral home to take my Birthright on our Honored Arena.  I’ve my doubts that this will be a fair combat, but this is not my concern.  As Blacko and Utaldain know, I am three days for the time that I must assume my position on the Dark Council.  I must renounce all in service to Neriak and our Lord, Innoruuk.  I must assume my Title as the Duke of the Dark and enjoy the power and privileges accorded to my Rank.  This…does not sit well with me.  I’ve had turbulent thoughts considering this matter, yet my heart is decided.  I will refute my claim to my Father’s Title and renounce my name Dy’Truin.”  This news was accepted with shock from Blacko and Utaldain, whose own families were of some of the Great Houses of Neriak.  Utaldain exclaimed, “Give up you name?!  Soulshiver, you’ve gone mad!!”  Blacko, equally disturbed said, “Brother, she is only a Elf! A paladin at that!!  Don’t get me wrong, Bro, she’s worth attention…but give up your Name?!  Your Title?!  By Innoruuk’s poisoned breath, give your bloody Title to me!!”  Itno, quietly said, “Brothers, matters of the heart are complicated ones.  Soulshiver is entitled to his feelings, certainly if his love for Centuri is reciprocated, we could all call Soulshiver a lucky elf.”  To this the trio of rogues added their agreement.  Utaldain had overcome his initial shock, but Blacko was visibly suffering.  “Peace, Brother, I wish I had the power to explain her meaning to me…yet, such words escape me as they have never been uttered.  Just trust me.”  Blacko, to his credit, nodded and gave his assent.  “Yours will be the task, Brothers, to ensure that I’ve some moments alone with my brother.  I will, I fitfully pray, have some others that will witness what I’ve to say to that worthless whelp.  Be ready, for I will be in dire need of the strength of your arms.  Now please, Anouris, do me a favor and poison my drink with a sleeping draught.  I fear I will be needing it this night, for on the morrow Brothers, we prove Blood Circle…”<br>
<br>
From the Dark Annuals of Soulshiver, recorded by House Dy'Truin historian, Mx'thal, assigned to catalogue the Heir of the Darks Life-history.<br>
<br>
